        "body": "# Add Interactive TUI Menu for TermiFlux\r\n\r\nThis PR implements two interactive Text User Interface (TUI) versions for TermiFlux, addressing issue #3.\r\n\r\n## What's Included:\r\n\r\n### 1. `TermiFlux_TUI.sh` - Professional Dialog Version\r\n- Uses `dialog` for native pop-up menus\r\n- Arrow key navigation\r\n- Professional appearance\r\n- Graceful cancel handling\r\n\r\n### 2. `TermiFlux_SimpleTUI.sh` - Enhanced Text Version  \r\n- No external dependencies\r\n- Visual borders and emojis\r\n- Input validation with looping\r\n- Works on all systems\r\n\r\n## Benefits:\r\n- **Better user experience** than original basic menu\r\n- **Visual feedback** and clear options\r\n- **Input validation** prevents errors\r\n- **Maintains all original functionality**\r\n\r\n## Testing:\r\nBoth versions have been tested and work correctly with all menu options.\r\n\r\nFixes #3\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n## New Features\n* Introduced Terminal UI application for macOS architecture switching between ARM64 (Apple Silicon) and x86_64 (via Rosetta 2)\n* Implemented automatic Rosetta 2 detection and installation\n* Added convenient shell aliases for quick architecture toggling\n* Provided both simplified and enhanced UI options for user preference\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
